{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "05", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "13", "M": "03", "S": "10"}}, "news": [{"title": "Chandigarh wants to rise higher but can its roads take the load?", "para": "Chandigarh's ambitious development plans, including higher building limits and mixed land use, are raising serious concerns about traffic congestion.  Official reports and resident objections highlight a critical gap: the city is densifying without a clear plan for its overloaded transport infrastructure.  Decades-old warnings about saturated roads and a lack of mass transit are now a stark reality, with private vehicles dominating and speeds plummeting.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/chandigarhs-urban-dilemma-higher-density-vs-traffic-chaos/132191835?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1679817/132191835.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Ludhiana: LIT slashes reserve price to \u20b9182 crore in fresh bid to auction its commercial building", "para": "Ludhiana Improvement Trust has slashed the reserve price of a prime commercial building by \u20b915 crore to \u20b9182 crore in a fresh e-auction, hoping to attract buyers after previous attempts failed. The 18-year-old, abandoned property, featuring extensive commercial space and parking, has suffered from neglect. LIT is also considering price cuts for other properties due to poor market response.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/ludhiana-improvement-trust-reduces-auction-price-of-prime-commercial-building-to-182-crore/132191743?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-192338/132191743.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "NCLT directs Entertainment City to register minority stake in favour of Parmesh Construction", "para": "Insolvency tribunal NCLT has greenlit Parmesh Construction Company's acquisition of a 4.26% stake in Entertainment City, dismissing Unitech Holding's objections. The tribunal ruled that the share transfer by minority investors was valid, despite Unitech's claims of violated shareholder agreements. This decision stems from a broader 100% disinvestment process for Entertainment City, where Parmesh Construction emerged as the successful bidder.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/nclt-rules-in-favor-of-parmesh-construction-against-unitech-in-entertainment-city-stake-dispute/132191679?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-448636/132191679.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}